"""End-to-end UI test: table reservation scenario through the React frontend.

Extension of ``skel-test-pizza-reservation``. After the agent adds
the backend reservation endpoints (via the per-service ``./ai``
agent) AND the React UI for booking + restaurant confirmation, a
Playwright spec drives:

    1. CLIENT logs into the web UI.
    2. CLIENT picks a date + time and submits a reservation.
    3. RESTAURANT logs in via a separate browser context and
       confirms the reservation.
    4. CLIENT refreshes the status view and sees the confirmation.

Same scaffolding as ``skel-test-pizza-web``: re-uses generation +
sanitisers + selective rollback from the existing runners, then
installs Playwright into the React service and runs one spec.
"""

